  "explanation": "The defendant abused a position of trust as an accountant to embezzle $25,000 from their employer, which constitutes a serious breach of professional duty. However, mitigating factors must be taken into account: the defendant has no prior criminal record and has made a good-faith effort to partially pay back the embezzled funds, demonstrating remorse. Accordingly, a sentence at the lower end of the sentencing guidelines is appropriate to balance deterrence with rehabilitation.",
  "verdict": 6
}
